EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to Medicaid; requiring Medicaid to provide
coverage for medical respite care for persons
experiencing homelessness, if federal financial
participation is available; requiring the development of a
model for providing such medical respite care; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Department of Health and Human Services to
2 administer Medicaid. (NRS 422.270) If federal financial participation is available,
3 section 1 of this bill requires the Director of the Department, effective July 1, 2027,
4 to include coverage under Medicaid for medical respite care provided to persons
5 experiencing homelessness by a facility that meets certain requirements. Section 1
6 requires the Department to apply to the Federal Government for any waiver or
7 amendment necessary to receive federal financial participation to provide such
8 coverage. Section 1 defines “medical respite care” to refer to certain medical care
9 and support services. Section 1 additionally requires the Division of Health Care
10 Financing and Policy of the Department to coordinate with the Division of Public
11 and Behavioral Health of the Department to develop a model for providing medical
12 respite care to persons experiencing homelessness. Section 2 of this bill makes a
13 conforming change to indicate that the provisions of section 1 will be administered
14 in the same manner as the provisions of existing law governing Medicaid.
