1 Section 1. Chapter 422 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. To the extent that federal financial participation is
4 available, the Director shall include under Medicaid coverage for
5 medical respite care, for not more than 90 days during any 12-
6 month period, provided by a facility that meets the requirements of
7 subsection 2 to persons experiencing homelessness. Such medical
8 respite care must include, without limitation:
9 (a) Case management, including, without limitation,
10 development of case plans;
11 (b) Coordination of care;
12 (c) Behavioral health services and referrals for such services;
13 (d) Food and housing services and support;
14 (e) Storage and management of medications;
15 (f) Acute and post-acute medical care;
16 (g) Care before or after a medical procedure or operation,
17 including, without limitation, wound care;
18 (h) Transportation to and from scheduled medical
19 appointments;
20 (i) Evaluation, assessment and immediate interventions for
21 medical, psychological, vocational, cultural, social or
22 environmental factors; and
23 (j) Care for and education on substance use disorders.
24 2. A facility that wishes to receive reimbursement through
25 Medicaid pursuant to subsection 1 for medical respite care must:
26 (a) Operate in accordance with the model developed pursuant
27 to subsection 4.
28 (b) Be staffed 24 hours each day, 7 days each week by
29 providers of health care who are qualified to provide medical
30 respite care and have received training concerning:
31 (1) Trauma-informed care;
32 (2) De-escalation techniques; and
33 (3) Mental health first aid, including, without limitation:
34 (I) Recognizing the symptoms of a mental illness or
35 substance use disorder;
36 (II) Providing initial assistance to persons experiencing
37 a mental health or substance use crisis;
38 (III) Guiding persons requiring assistance with mental
39 health issues, including, without limitation, persons experiencing
40 a mental health or substance use crisis, to professionals qualified
41 to provide such assistance;
